  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which is actually cheaper?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        AXA is 10-15% cheaper when you exclude US coverage. But when you add US coverage to AXA (30-40% premium increase), Aetna is often comparable or cheaper—with better US network integration. Compare equivalent coverage, not headline prices.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are CVS prescription benefits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Aetna's CVS Health connection means you can fill prescriptions at CVS pharmacies with integrated coverage and competitive pricing. This is valuable for Americans who fill prescriptions during US visits. AXA uses standard prescription reimbursement without pharmacy network integration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I have a pre-existing condition?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Aetna uses full medical underwriting—they review your history and may cover, exclude, or rate up conditions. AXA offers moratorium underwriting (no health questions, but conditions not covered for 24 months) or full underwriting depending on the plan.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which has better mental health coverage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Aetna has a slight edge in mental health coverage, but neither matches BUPA Global's full parity. If mental health is your top priority, consider BUPA. If it's one factor among many, Aetna provides solid coverage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is EU Solvency II?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Solvency II is the EU's insurance regulatory framework—one of the most rigorous globally. It requires insurers to maintain capital reserves, implement risk management, and provide transparency. AXA operates under this framework, providing robust consumer protections.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I switch between them later?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Yes, but switching involves new underwriting. Any conditions you develop become pre-existing for the new insurer. Both offer guaranteed renewability, so staying with your current provider avoids this issue. Choose thoughtfully based on your anticipated needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

